<LP>
   STEVEN L. GLAUBERMAN, a former associate at the New York
law firm of Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher &amp; Flom gave
inside-trading information to his sister, Lori Glauberman,
the government has alleged. Friday's edition misstated where
Ms. Glauberman allegedly got her information.
   (See: "U.S. Files Charges in Insider-Trade Case Involving
Ex-Scadden Takeover Lawyer" -- WSJ Aug. 10, 1990)
</LP>
<TEXT>
   ---
   THE SALARY for H.J. Heinz Co. Chairman Anthony J.F.
O'Reilly in the fiscal year ended May 2 was $708,117 in cash
compensation and $2.6 million in bonuses. In Friday's
edition, Mr. O'Reilly's salary was misstated.
   (See: "Heinz'z O'Reilly Signs 5-Year Contract, Receives
Options to Buy 4 Million Shares" -- WSJ Aug. 10, 1990)
</TEXT>
